Program: Outlook
Title: 01/01/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p005kjcs
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 4 Jan 2010
The BBC's Olga Betko tracks down the five Ukrainian sailors who were captured by Somali pirates and held captive for months on their ship the MV Faina. Listen as they share their memories of that ill-fated voyage with a cargo of tanks, rocket-launchers and small arms.